                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="w-full text-left px-4 py-3 flex justify-between items-center faq-question"
                  >
                    <span class="font-medium"
                      >Should I use GCS or just “altered mental status”?</span
                    >
                    <svg
                      class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transition-transform"
                      viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                      fill="none"
                    >
                      <path
                        d="M6 8l4 4 4-4"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                      />
                    </svg>
                  </button>
                  <div class="px-4 pb-3 hidden faq-answer">
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                      The original Sepsis-3 definition used
                      <strong>GCS &lt; 15</strong> as the criterion. In
                      practice, many clinicians use either a documented GCS &lt;
                      15 or any
                      <strong>acute change in mental status</strong> from
                      baseline (e.g., new confusion, agitation, decreased
                      responsiveness). This calculator allows you to record GCS
                      and/or mark an acute change, and then decide whether the
                      criterion is met.
                    </p>
