                    </svg>
                  </button>
                  <div class="px-4 pb-3 hidden faq-answer">
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                      No. qSOFA is a <strong>risk stratification</strong> tool
                      only. It does not specify treatment. Management should
                      follow local sepsis guidelines (e.g., Surviving Sepsis
                      Campaign), including timely antibiotics, source control,
                      fluid resuscitation, vasopressors, and organ support as
                      indicated.
